as independent of sex, age, and comorbid illnesses and despite similar nasopharyngeal SARS-CoV-2 viral loads. Furthermore, there was reduced levels of key inflammatory proteins in circulation in patients with GI symptoms.\nConclusions\nThese data highlight the absence of a proinflammatory response in the GI tract despite detection of SARS-CoV-2. In parallel, reduced mortality in patients with COVID-19 presenting with GI symptoms was observed. A potential role of the GI tract in attenuating SARS-CoV-2\u2013associated inflammation needs to be further examined.", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "Livanos, Alexandra E.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Jha, Divya", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Cossarini, Francesca", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Gonzalez-Reiche, Ana S.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Tokuyama, Minami", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Aydillo, Teresa", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Parigi, Tommaso L.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Ladinsky, Mark S.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Ramos, Irene", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Dunleavy, Katie", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Lee, Brian", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Dixon, Rebekah E.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Chen, Steven T.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Martinez-Delgado, Gustavo", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Nagula, Satish", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Bruce, Emily A.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Ko, Huaibin M.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Glicksberg, Benjamin S.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Nadkarni, Girish", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Pujadas, Elisabet", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Reidy, Jason", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Naymagon, Steven", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Grinspan, Ari", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Ahmad, Jawad", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Tankelevich, Michael", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Bram, Yaron", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Gordon, Ronald", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Shar